<Author>rsm25
<Content>Great location. Not as clean as one might want. Not associated with the Ritz Carlton in any way shape or form, something that becomes evident upon arrival, but has a great central location in Barcelona. Room service lacked basic foodstuffs, like bread and ham. We found a dirty condom under the bed, left by a previous occupant, which we discovered while looking for our 3 year old's shoe. Management offered to send a maid to clean the room again, nothing else. Nice bathroom, decent size TV, cute little terrace. Pretty small room. Very thin walls. Good amenities, plenty of towels. Terrible, super-hard mattresses. One of the least comfortable nights I have ever spent anywhere -- and I slept in Grand Central Station once in the 80s. Did I mention the dirty condom under the bed? 
