<Author>HilaryManchester
<Content>Ritz in name only Reviewer Manchester EnglandJust spent two days in Barcelona with the family at the Ritz Roger de Lluria hotel. Not impressed at all. Let me start by saying that the location is in fact excellent, and the rooms of a reasonable standard for the price, if somewhat lack lustered.But the staff (other than an excellent Italian concierge) were completely useless. Surly, lacking any idea how to run a front desk with a complete lack of working English. I can understand this from a small hotel off the beaten track, but not a so called 4 star in the centre of a major European city. Just to give you one instance, we have a party of six, over 11 pieces of luggage, which we had to man handle in the lifts ourselves because the porter forgot to callFront desk said he was busy, but porter said that he just forgot !!!!When he finally arrived he failed to get us the taxis we required, leaving us to wonder in the street searching in the rain.Breakfast was the only meal we took, poor and lacking variety. If you wanted hot tea, you had to make it your self, pouring out hot water from a communal hot jug.There are much better hotels, at a similar cost to stay at in Barcelona than this one. Avoid it !!!!!!! 
