<Content>Don't bother Positive:1) Central Location2) Large rooms by European standardsNegative:1) A little rundown2) Ridiculous telephone prices3) Arrogant, unfriendly receptionAs a business traveller, I see a lot of hotels - good and poor. Check-In was ok, but ist was the first time, that I got a room, that wasn't made. Got a new one, no problem. Rooms are old and a bit rundown; not too clean. Breakfast was good except for rancid raw ham and salami and constant asking of staff for room number (they didn't do much else). Unpleasant check-out: While talking to me the manager on duty was also on the, very unfriendly. The mini-bar rates charged me on the bill where higher than on the list in the room. What really surprised me was the cost of a 3-minute local call: more than five Euro for two units. For me that's clearly rip-off. In total, I CANNOT recommend this hotel. 
