<Author>emmie_2006
<Content>Lovely Hotel, Central Location This hotel was in an excellent location about a 10-15min walk from Passeig de Gracia/ La Ramblas (The two central streets of downtown Barcelona). The hotel itself was well maintained and had a nice decor. The reception staff were very helpful and courteous which made our stay even more enjoyable. The rooms were of a good size and had a well stocked bathroom even complete with bathrobes. The only let down was the buffet breakfast. It was of a poor standard, not much variety and the buffet was constantly running out of food which was quickly replaced when the staff were alerted. All in all a great place to stay but don't bother with the breakfast. 
