<Author>dcdude
<Content>Old - I Hated It...But Wife Loved It I have to give the Hotel Ritz Barcelona (no affiliation with The Ritz-Carlton Hotel chain) a neutral rating because my wife loved it...and I hated it.It's old. Yes, as the previous reviewer wrote, it is in a great location...because it's old. If you like Old Europe feel, then this is the place for you. I like new and modern, so -- when we had lunch at the Ritz Carlton's Hotel Arts -- I knew that we had made a mistake. (Hotel Arts is gorgeous, by the way. Even my wife acknowledged that it was beautiful.)Our room at the Hotel Ritz was old. I just hated it.The concierge staff was good. They recommended dinner at a particular restaurant (I don't have the name in front of me right now) that both my wife and I enjoyed very much. We appreciated that recommendation. Breakfast at Hotel Ritz was pretty average. Not great...but not bad.My wife would stay here again...but I won't. :) 
